rt of the Tality spinoff of that consulting group, that was subsequently reacquired by Cadence.  Russ has vast experience introducing new technology to customers, and working jointly with the customers to quantify the value of the technology throughout their overall businesses.   Russ also was regional GM for Ionics Inc (acquired by GE) and held previous sales and business development positions at Hercules Inc (now merged into Ashland Inc).Russ received a B.S. degree in Chemical Engineering from Lehigh University and a Master of Business Administration from California State Polytechnic University.  Russ is located in Southern California. Russ is a senior business executive with over 30 years of experience in the technology space managing new products, go to market teams, sales and business development. He has been in the software space for over 18 years.  At Security First Corp. (SFC), Russ is leading the company’s growth into the cloud market space by developing and bringing to the market products and client relationships where SecureParser® technology can add value to cloud infrastructure and data storage.  Russ is resolute in his belief that data is a valuable asset and should be protected from theft, loss or subpoena, and that doing so should not prevent rightful owners from accessing it or become a burdensome process. During his time at SFC, Russ has defined product requirements, helped create and launch several new products, co-authored several patents, and assisted with obtaining customer feedback for strategic planning.  He currently also manages SFC’s OEM cloud product relationships and was successful in closing contracts to provide SPx core technology to SFC’s OEM customer base. Prior to joining SFC, Russ worked at various software startups whose focus was developing innovative and breakthrough technologies for their industries. While growing those businesses, Russ helped each position itself so that they became acquisition targets.  Russ also lead the Sou