orate marketing functions, including business strategy, partnership management, branding, advertising, performance measurement and analysis and customer loyalty. Prior, Mr. Karzak was SVP of marketing at Countrywide Financial Corporation. At Countrywide, he was responsible for strategic development, design, and implementation of all online and offline marketing, advertising, and public relations initiatives for Countrywide's insurance and banking entities. Mr. Karzak has also held senior marketing leadership positions at MBNA America (now Bank of America, N.A.), Wachovia Bank, N.A., Mutual of Omaha, and Harrah's Entertainment.Mr. Karzak graduated Summa Cum Laude with an MBA degree from Wilmington University and received his BS degree from the University of Baltimore. John Karzak is a dynamic visionary with 18+ years of diversified marketing expertise in growing consumer markets in multiple verticals for Fortune 100 companies. As a senior-level marketing executive, Mr. Karzak has extensive experience and exceptional success in the conceptualization, creative planning, deployment, and management of full-scale, high-impact, B2C and B2B marketing campaigns. He is recognized as an innovator in traditional, digital and mobile marketing with an unrivaled ability to blend advanced analytics, technical acumen and practical judgment in the development and execution of strategic plans.Prior to joining Security First Corp., Mr. Karzak was co-founder and managing director of Consent Media, a digital marketing agency specializing in the emerging channels of digital, mobile, and social media marketing. He held overall responsibility for the client partnership team and leads the translation of client objectives into marketing strategies that win new business, influence consumer spending, improve market position and increase revenue.Prior to joining Consent Media, Mr. Karzak was Chief Marketing Officer at Affinity Financial Corporation.  In this capacity, he was responsible for all 