es division of American Airlines including the company's revenue management reporting system.John Mumaugh Senior Vice President of Business Development Rick Orsini has more than 30 years of Information Systems experience with a focus on developing and implementing high volume mission critical transaction processing systems. At Security First Corp., Rick has led the development of the SecureParser products and a number of prototype applications using the underlying cryptographic splitting technology.  He is a co-author on many of the 220+ issued, granted or pending patents in areas that include data security and data availability for data in motion and data at rest; Internet and cloud security; as well as key management, dispersed storage, collaboration and connectivity.Prior to joining SFC, Rick played a key role in the overall deployment and integration of TrustEngine, the forerunner of the SecureParser. He managed the development the TrustEngine Java-based client and vendor software, which provided connectivity to the Linux, LDAP and XML-based TrustEngine. He also built and led a team of developers in the implementation of patent pending technology for Internet security, using encryption techniques, custom SSL, enveloping and chain verification to secure and store biometric and other secure information to geographically dispersed locations.Previously Rick was a Sr. Director at PC Service Source, a high-volume, next-day provider of replacement computer parts for the PC Service industry. As the first full-time IS employee at PC Service Source, he was responsible for all IS infrastructure, operational and software development, procurement, implementation, and support during the company's most rapid revenue growth.Rick was previously the co-founder and President of Orsini & Burns, Inc., a Boston area software development and consulting company specializing in point-of-sale, wholesale distribution, and temporary employment solutions. Rick Orsini has more than 30 years 